What: 
Docker is an opensource containerization platform that allows you to package an application with all
its dependencies into a lightweight until called a portable containers. It was
originally generated 2013 
---------------------------
Why: 
previously, application often failed when moved between environment means from 
developer lappy to a production server, we commonly know ->it works on my machine 
so docker solve this problem to by packaging the application code, runtime, system
libraries, Dependencies, configuration into a container that has own filesystem
and run isolated consistently. 
-------------------------------
container: 
Lightweight and isolated from other applications and faster from virtual machine
and these are built from a docker image.unlike virtual machine, container shares
the host kernal, making them much more efficient
---------------------------------
docker architecture
docker client commands in terminal- who sends request to docker daemon and docker
daemon execute these commands...
docker build 
docker pull 
docker run 
----------------------------------
docker daemon - works as an engine, it will run in background  as dockered process
it will build images and run the containers and create network and manage the 
volumes, basically it does the actual work !
---------------------------------
docker registry - "Image store"
this is a storage where we keep docker images called docker hub
---------------------------------
docker image: It is a readymade template or blueprint of image, wcich create container
includes: App code, Runtime node,python, liabraries, dependencies, configurations,
this is read only,this is immutable, never change
---------------------------------------
container - Running App, this is the runnig version of an image
docker run any_image ->create a container from imageand run, container is light
weight, isolated and can start, stop and delete
-----------------------------------
dockerfile- this is an instructions text file
-which base image will use
-which code should be copied
-which command should run
ex: FROM node:18
WORKDIR /app
COPY ..
RUN npm install
CMD ["node", "app.js"]
