-----------docker image layer-----
container ->layer1 ->layer2 ->Base layer(linux)
when we create a layer, a new writable layer(called container layer) is added on top of
underlying base layer called linux , the layer comes b/w base images to layer are immutable
they can change , we can only change container layer...
like if we work on two images then they have theor own layers so they are immutable or can't
change an it called already exist... 
-------------port binding---------------
docker run -p 8080:3306 image_name
, yeh dono image me joh common por hai yeh container port hai, host port nhi hai
like host port would be different even container ports are same... 
mapping ke process ko port binding kehte hai...
docker run -d -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=secretnew --name mysql-latest -p8080:3306 mysql
docker run -d -e MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD=secretold --name mysql-older -p3000:3306 mysql
now we have two different container whcih is bind with two different host container
