---------docker vs vm--------
1.hardware ->2.host kernal os ->3.application layer 
so here docker use only application layer and share host and virtulaization on application layer only 
but in vm , it takes kernal host(2) + application layer ->so it becomes heavy and docker is light-weight
---ADVANTAGE OF Docker is it is based on linux, so mosty images are linux based , so can we run
these into window and macos, so here we use docker desktop, this is add a hypervisor layer to
our system , so easily we can run container easilt on window and mac, basically docker desktop 
containes linux based virtual machine which helps us run a container...so when we work on docker
in production so we prefer linux based os , so it becomes easy and compatible
